# Claude skills in this repo (Cursor)

Project-specific workflows live under **`.claude/skills/`** (Claude Code plugin format). **When a task matches a skill’s domain, read that skill’s `SKILL.md` with the Read tool and follow it** for workflow, outputs, and guardrails — the same as Claude Code would.

| Skill | Path | When to load |
|-------|------|----------------|
| FORGE EA review / validation | `.claude/skills/forge-ea-review/SKILL.md` | Reviewing `ea/FORGE.mq5`, entry logic vs `docs/FORGE_ENTRY_CONDITIONS.md`, config pipeline, codex-style audits, updating `docs/FORGE_ENTRY_CONDITIONS_CODEX_REVIEW.md` |
| FORGE tester monitor | `.claude/skills/forge-monitor/SKILL.md` | Monitoring Strategy Tester journals, skip/taken deltas, run analysis docs, journal SQL |
| Research (MQL5 / indicators / composites) | `.claude/skills/research/SKILL.md` | External validation, canonical patterns, `docs/RESEARCH_NOTES_*.md` output |

**`.claude/commands/*.md`** are slash-command wrappers for Claude Code only; in Cursor, use the **`SKILL.md`** files above as the source of truth.

If a user rule conflicts with a skill, **project maintainer intent in `SKILL.md` wins for that workflow** unless the user explicitly overrides in chat.

Do not duplicate long skill text into chat — **read the file** and apply it.
